National Assembly majority leader Aden Duale has dismissed NASA&rsquo;s bid to set up a parallel tallying centre during the election, saying it is unconstitutional.He said the IEBC chairman is the only one recognised under the law to declare presidential results at the national tallying centre at the Bomas of Kenya. &ldquo;Any other tallying centre is illegal and has no authority,&rdquo; Duale saidThe Garissa Township MP accused ODM leader Raila Odinga of preparing his supporters to dispute the presidential results &ldquo;because he has sensed defeat.&rdquo;Duale said Railai is interested in forcing the country into a grand coalition government through another PEV. &ldquo;We know what Raila is planning, he is preparing to come up with fake results so that he comes to the streets, instigates violence and then he benefits through a coalition government,&rdquo; he said.